### `refactor`: Switch from Create React App to Vite
This PR finishes moving the whole project from Create React App (CRA) over to Vite.
Vite is way faster for both development and production builds.

---
### Speed Boost
Build times dropped big time:

| Build Tool | Build Time (Total) |
| ---------- | ------------------ |
| CRA        | ~10.86 seconds     |
| Vite       | ~2.67 seconds      |
```bash
# Vite - time npm run build
npm run build  5.18s user 0.73s system 221% cpu 2.668 total

# CRA - time npm run build
npm run build  21.52s user 2.14s system 217% cpu 10.860 total
```

That’s about a **75% faster build**.
Definitely feels snappier when working locally and also speeds up our deployment!

---

### What Changed?
A quick rundown of the key updates:
- **Dependencies & Scripts:**
    - Removed `react-scripts` and Babel packages since we don’t need CRA anymore.
    - Added `vite` and `@vitejs/plugin-react` to dev dependencies.
    - Updated `start` and `build` scripts to use Vite commands.
    - Removed CRA-specific scripts like `eject`.
      
| Package               | Why removed                                                                |
| --------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `react-scripts`       | CRA-only, not needed in Vite                                               |
| All `@babel/*`        | Not needed — Vite uses `esbuild` and plugins                               |
| `react-error-overlay` | Specific to CRA error handling                                             |
| `browserslist`        | Optional — if needed, move config to `.browserslistrc` or `vite.config.js` |
| `"eject"` script      | Only exists in CRA                                                         |

- **Config & Project Setup:**    
    - Added `vite.config.js` for React plugin and SVG support.
    - Moved `index.html` from `/public` to the project root, updated script tag for Vite.
      index.js file changes
		Changed index.js entry point from /public to ./
		 **Removed** CRA-specific placeholders
			Changed:
			`<link rel="manifest" href="%PUBLIC_URL%/manifest.json" />`
			 Replaced with:
			`<link rel="manifest" href="/site.webmanifest" />`
		
		Removed redundancy in link and meta tag i.e. -
		```js
		<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
		<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
		```
		
		
		Added Vite entry script
		```js
		<script type="module" src="/src/main.jsx"></script>
		```

    - Fixed public asset paths — no more `%PUBLIC_URL%` stuff, switched to absolute paths like `/favicon.ico`.

- **SVG Imports:**    
    - CRA’s `import { ReactComponent as ... }` doesn’t work in Vite out of the box.
    - Added `vite-plugin-svgr` and switched SVG imports to use the `?react` suffix, e.g. `import Logo from "./logo.svg?react"`.
      
    -  StyledLink Fixes and SVG Import Compatibility
		- **Renamed `StyledLink.js` to `StyledLink.jsx`** to resolve a JSX syntax error and follow proper file naming conventions.
		- **Installed and configured `vite-plugin-svgr`** to support importing SVGs as React components in a Vite environment.
		- **Updated SVG imports in `Header.jsx`** to use the `?react` suffix:
		    `import PollinationsLogo from "../assets/logo/logo-text.svg?react"; import LogoIconBlack from "../assets/logo/logo-icon-black.svg?react";`
		    This ensures compatibility with Vite’s handling of SVGs and replaces the unsupported `ReactComponent` syntax from Create React App.


- **Deployment Updates:**    
    - Changed Netlify build command to `npm run build`.
    - Updated publish folder from `build` to `dist` (Vite’s default).

- **General Cleanup:**    
    - **Renamed `.js` to `.jsx`** for files containing JSX across:
      `src/Home`, `src/components`, `src/utils`, etc.
    - **Updated Import Paths**
	    - Adjusted all import statements to reference `.jsx` files.
    - Renamed main entry from `src/index.js` to `src/main.jsx`.
    - Ran `npm audit fix` and installed `vite-tsconfig-paths` for smoother imports.

---
### Environment Variables
No environment variables using `REACT_APP_` were found, so no changes needed there.

---

### ✅ Checklist
- [x]  Dev server runs with `npm run start` without errors    
- [x] Production build completes successfully
- [x] All existing features work as before (no regressions)
- [x]  Build time is noticeably faster
- [x]  Hot Module Replacement (HMR) works in development
- [x]  Netlify deploys the app successfully











